69.9	Ghostwriter	Ghostwriter	A ghostwriter is a writer who writes books, articles, stories, reports, or other texts that are officially credited to another person. Celebrities, executives, and political leaders often hire ghostwriters to draft or edit autobiographies, magazine articles, or other written material. In music, ghostwriters are used in film score composition, as well as for writing songs and lyrics for popular music genres.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Hrcraad.jpg/150px-Hrcraad.jpg
